{
  "description": "A dramatic, low-angle view of a powerful waterfall cascading down a sheer granite cliff face. The water appears as a white, foamy stream against the dark, textured rock. The base of the falls is filled with large, wet boulders and a small, murky pool of water. The cliff face is immense and weathered, showing layers and patterns of erosion. A sliver of pale blue sky is visible at the very top, partially obscured by wisps of cloud. The overall lighting is dramatic, with strong contrast between the bright white water and the dark rock. The foreground is dominated by dark, wet rocks, leading the eye towards the powerful waterfall. There is vegetation visible clinging to the rocks.",
